-- North Sea Statfjord Crude Loadings Stable in September at 4 Lots
-- B y   L a u r a   H u r s t
-- 2013-08-05T12:31:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-05/north-sea-statfjord-crude-loadings-stable-in-september-at-4-lots.html
North Sea Statfjord crude exports are
scheduled at four cargoes in September, unchanged from August, a
loading program obtained by Bloomberg News showed.  Exports will total 3.255 million barrels, or 108,500
barrels a day, compared with 105,000 barrels a day this month.
September shipments will comprise three lots of 800,000 barrels
and one of 855,000 barrels.  Loading programs are monthly schedules of crude shipments
compiled by field operators to allow buyers and sellers to plan
their supply and trading activities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Hurst in London at 
 lhurst3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
